               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220417-28-person310">
                  BENJAMIN 
                  HEMMING
               <interp inst="t18220417-28-person310" type="surname" value="HEMMING"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220417-28-person310" type="given" value="BENJAMIN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220417-28-person310" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a porter to Messrs. Harbons. On the 27th of March the prisoner came in for a pair of hinges - I was coming into the shop and saw him put a parcel containing seven brass hinges into his pocket - I told him to lay the parcel down; he said he had nothing belonging to me - he was standing where the hinges were. My master took hold of him, and in the scuffle I saw him drop them. I picked them up.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220417-28-person311">
                  SAMUEL 
                  HARBON
               <interp inst="t18220417-28-person311" type="surname" value="HARBON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220417-28-person311" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220417-28-person311" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am in partnership with 
               <persName id="t18220417-28-person312">
                  John 
                  Harbon
               <interp inst="t18220417-28-person312" type="surname" value="Harbon"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220417-28-person312" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220417-28-person312" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The prisoner came in while another person was serving at the counter, and went to the further end of the shop were the hinges are kept, and pulled a pair out.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I never saw them.</p>
               <p>
